Package com.netcracker.tc.model

Test cases configuration package.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Observer Test configuration state observer.
Type Parameter type with restrictions.
 

Class Summary
Configuration Test cases configuration, contains list of test configurations, sends events about configuration changes on all levels (test cases configuration, test case, test scenario, test scenario parameter).
Output Test scenario output result, can be referensed as parameter value for further scenarios within this test case.
Parameter Scenario input parameter.
Scenario Atomic test step, describes test scenario, that has input parameters and output results.
Schema Prototype for test scenarios.
Schemas Test cases schemas.
Test One test case configuration, consists of test scenarios.
 

Enum Summary
Observer.Event  
 

Package com.netcracker.tc.model Description

Test cases configuration package. Configuration contains Test* Test contains Scenario* Scenario contains Parameter* and Output* Schemas contains Schema* Schema is prototype of Scenario

Creating new parameter types

To create new parameter type you need:
  1. Implement Type
  2. Implement EditorWidget
  3. Implement reader/writer modules.

    For XML storage you need to implement:

    • ValueReader
    • ValueWriter
  4. Implement TypeReader
  5. (optional) Create type-specific annotations with @Target({PARAMETER,FIELD})

See Also:
com.netcracker.tc.types.standard
